




TY  - JOUR
T1  - Cognitive Process as a Basis for MIS and DSS Design
AU  - Ramaprasad, Arkalgud
Y1  - 1987/02/01
PY  - 1987
DA  - 1987/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.33.2.139
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.33.2.139
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 139
EP  - 148
VL  - 33
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Cognitive process research can provide specific, operational guidelines for MIS/DSS design by delineating the specific influences on managers' cognitive processes in sensing, formulating, and solving problems. The paper integrates some of the considerable body of literature on these processes in the framework of Piaget's model to illustrate the type of guidelines cognitive process research can provide. It also delineates three topical areas for future research: (a) Choice of Logico-Mathematical-Structures (LMSs), (b) Development of LMSs, and (c) Application/Attribution of LMSs to sense, formulate and solve problems, and describes how research in these areas can help improve the effectiveness of MIS/DSS.
AB  - Cognitive process research can provide specific, operational guidelines for MIS/DSS design by delineating the specific influences on managers' cognitive processes in sensing, formulating, and solving problems. The paper integrates some of the considerable body of literature on these processes in the framework of Piaget's model to illustrate the type of guidelines cognitive process research can provide. It also delineates three topical areas for future research: (a) Choice of Logico-Mathematical-Structures (LMSs), (b) Development of LMSs, and (c) Application/Attribution of LMSs to sense, formulate and solve problems, and describes how research in these areas can help improve the effectiveness of MIS/DSS.
